
libnetconf Example Applications
===============================

Programs available from this directory serve as simple examples of using
libnetconf for building NETCONF enabled applications. All examples provide
'-h' option that provides detailed user description.

To build examples, just type:

$ make


get
---

Retrieves configuration as well as status data of the device. It connects to
the specified host and executes NETCONF <get> operation. Optionally, user
can specify NETCONF subtree filter to retrieve only a specific part of the
configuration/status data.

notif
-----

Simple application that generates a NETCONF event on the NETCONF server side.
The event is logged into the NETCONF stream and can be replayed by a NETCONF
server to clients.
